The reset command requires exactly one argument: an 8-character closure hash. Missing arguments return a usage error with an example. On success it returns "Closure HASH resolved. Baseline updated." with exit code 0. Closures containing only broken-edge events are refused with an error directing the user to fix the scan. Unknown hashes return a "closure hash not found; run `drift todo` to list current closures" error. All forms exit 0 on success, 1 on error. See principles.friction.